title: Matador Cup squads, Matador BBQs Cup squads, Matador BBQs One-Day Cup squads, Australian state cricket teams
text:
SOME of the biggest names in Australian cricket will feature alongside the sport’s rising stars in this year’s Matador BBQs One-Day Cup.
Australia’s Test squad will miss the majority of the tournament while on tour in Bangladesh but that won’t stop this year’s domestic one-day competition from being a star-studded affair.
Already the likes of Shane Watson, James Faulkner and Josh Hazlewood have been named to play in the tournament, which will be run over three weeks with all matches played at Sydney suburban venues.
Click here for a full tournament schedule
Here is the list of squads for this year’s competition - this will be updated as each state names its playing group.
NEW SOUTH WALES
Moises Henriques (c), Sean Abbott, Doug Bollinger, Ryan Carters, Ed Cowan, Ryan Gibson, Chris Green, Josh Hazlewood, Josh Lalor, Nic Maddinson, Kurtis Patterson, Ben Rohrer, Gurinder Sandhu, Shane Watson.
Coach: Trent Johnston
QUEENSLAND
Chris Lynn (c), Cameron Boyce, Ben Cutting, Luke Feldman, Peter Forrest, Chris Hartley, Charlie Hemphrey, James Hopes, Marnus Labuschagne, Simon Milenko, Michael Neser, Nathan Reardon, Billy Stanlake, Mark Steketee.
Coach: Phil Jaques
Ben Cutting will be one of the leader’s of Queensland’s pace attack. Picture: Phil Hillyard. Source: News Corp Australia
TASMANIA
George Bailey (c), Jackson Bird, Xavier Doherty, Alex Doolan, Jake Doran, Ben Dunk, James Faulkner, Evan Gulbis, Hamish Kingston, Ryan Lees, Dominic Michael, Tim Paine, Sam Rainbird, Clive Rose
Co ach: Dan Marsh
CRICKET AUSTRALIA XI
Squad to be made up of 14 players who narrowly missed out on selection for the six state squads, as well as having the possibility of including national team players returning from injury.
Coach: Troy Cooley
SOUTH AUSTRALIA
Squad yet to be announced.
Coach: Jamie Siddons
VICTORIA
Squad yet to be announced.
Coach: David Saker
WESTERN AUSTRALIA
Squad yet to be announced.
Coach: Justin Langer
